  "prompt": "How do you find out what your zip code plus four is?",
  "response": "To find your ZIP+4 code, you can use the following methods:\n\n1. **USPS Website**:\n   - Visit the **United States Postal Service (USPS) ZIP Code Lookup Tool**: [https://tools.usps.com/go/ZipLookupAction!input.action](https://tools.usps.com/go/ZipLookupAction!input.action).\n   - Enter your address, including street, city, and state.\n   - The tool will provide your ZIP+4 code.\n\n2. **Call USPS**:\n   - Contact the USPS customer service at **1-800-ASK-USPS (1-800-275-8777)**.\n   - Provide your address, and they can give you the ZIP+4 code.\n\n3. **Online ZIP Code Tools**:\n   - Use third-party websites like **Smarty** or **Zip-Codes.com** to look up your ZIP+4 code by entering your address.\n\n4. **Check Your Mail**:\n   - Look at a piece of mail you\u2019ve received. The ZIP+4 code is often printed on the envelope or label in the address section.\n\nThe ZIP+4 code is a more specific version of the standard 5-digit ZIP code, providing additional information about a specific delivery route or building. It helps ensure more accurate and efficient mail delivery.",
